    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{4}{r-4}-\frac{3}{r+2}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{r+20}{\left(r-4\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}, \left(-\infty ,\infty \right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{4}{r-4}-\frac{3}{r+2}} 
      \amp = {\frac{4}{r-4}} \cdot \frac{(r+2)}{(r+2)} -\frac{3}{r+2} \cdot \frac{(r - 4)}{(r - 4)}  \\
      \amp = {\frac{4\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)-3\mathopen{}\left(r-4\right)}{\left(r-4\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{4r+8-3r+12}{\left(r-4\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{r+20}{\left(r-4\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
